- Not another minute!

253
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:22,000
Let's get to business.
I don't think anyone else is coming.

254
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:27,100
Father Galvan is in the kitchen.
We could finish watching the game.

255
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:29,400
No matter.
What were you talking about?

256
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:31,300
The game, Father. What else?

257
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:35,800
Father Amaro here was giving
us his view on celibacy.

258
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:38,800
Yes. If celibacy were optional...

259
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:42,400
...the church would avoid
a lot of trouble, don't you think?

260
00:22:44,100 --> 00:22:46,300
That's bullshit!

261
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:51,700
You'd sooner see a Mexican pope
than an end to the vow of celibacy.

262
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:53,400
Besides, what do we care?

263
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:56,900
What we care about now...

264
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:59,400
...are the accusations against you...

265
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,800
...Father Natalio.

266
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:05,700
- What is this about, Father?
- Clear the way, gentlemen!

267
00:23:05,700 --> 00:23:07,900
You've never tasted anything like this.

268
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:12,400
To welcome Father Amaro,
monsignor's favorite.

269
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:14,300
- Don't say that.
- And why not?

270
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:17,100
The bishop himself just told me so.

271
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:20,800
"This is my beloved son in whom
I take great pleasure."

272
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:24,600
- Don't blaspheme, Father Galvan.
- I'm sorry, but it's true.

273
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:29,100
Help yourselves, help yourselves.
You'll be licking your fingers.

274
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:34,300
Before we know it, they'll
name him adjunct bishop.

275
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,500
No.

276
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:41,200
I would like to know what
the accusations against me are.

277
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:47,900
The effects of your damned
liberation theology.

278
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:50,600
What does liberation theology
have to do...?

279
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:55,200
The Bishop has exact information,
very precise, Father Natalio...

280
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,800
...that you are protecting or helping...

281
00:23:57,900 --> 00:23:59,600
...guerrillas in your area.

282
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:01,400
What guerrillas?

283
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:05,300
You give them weapons,
or hide them for them.

284
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:07,700
Lies! That isn't true.

285
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:10,300
There are no guerrillas,
just drug lords.

286
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:13,900
The Aguilar brothers' drug traffickers.
Chato Aguilar's men.

287
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:18,500
- I'm talking about guerrillas.
- I'm talking about traffickers.

288
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:22,800
The kind who invade peasant lands,
force people to plant poppies...

289
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:26,100
...and threaten or kill them
if they refuse to work for them.

290
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:27,700
Gunmen and drug lords.

291
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:30,800
They are in my community
and they murder my people!

292
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:34,200
The bishop knows well of your
helping the guerrillas.

293
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:38,300
Then the bishop knows Chato Aguilar
launders money with donations.

294
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:40,600
All for your damn hospital center.

295
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:43,500
- You don't understand anything!
- I understand it all!

296
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:45,900
I know what goes on in my community.

297
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:51,300
Well, if you won't listen to me,
face the consequences, Father Natalio.

298
00:24:56,600 --> 00:25:01,200
Don't spoil our gathering, Natalio.
Let's have a good time.

299
00:25:20,900 --> 00:25:24,000
- I'm drunk as a skunk.
- I'll hold him on this side.

300
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:25,300
One, two...

301
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:31,000
But how about those <i>chiles rellenos</i>?

302
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:32,800
- Weren't they amazing?
- Yes.

303
00:25:32,900 --> 00:25:35,500
Especially for you...

304
00:25:36,100 --> 00:25:38,000
...God's favorite.

305
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:40,000
Thank you, Galvan.

306
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:43,500
Careful.

307
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:54,900
I would like you to visit
my community...

308
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:58,800
...up near the mountains,
so you could see how we work.

309
00:25:58,900 --> 00:26:01,800
What's that you said
about the donations?

310
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,600
I suspect it, but I don't really know.

311
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,200
I guess I went too far, right?

312
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:37,500
Excuse me.

313
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,900
Why not anymore?

314
00:26:48,300 --> 00:26:49,800
You know.

315
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:53,800
But I could come
when he is saying mass.

316
00:26:55,500 --> 00:26:58,100
Don't try my patience, for God's sake.

317
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:02,300
Or you could come to my house
when Amelia isn't home.

318
00:27:07,100 --> 00:27:09,400
You don't care about me anymore?

319
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:16,100
Excuse me, Father.

320
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:19,300
- Do you have any clothes to wash?
- I washed them myself. Thanks.

321
00:27:19,500 --> 00:27:22,200
I'm so glad to see you, Father,
because...

322
00:27:23,700 --> 00:27:26,300
...well, I wanted to...

323
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:27,700
...ask you a favor.

324
00:27:30,300 --> 00:27:32,000
It's Amelia, Father.

325
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:37,000
She broke up with her boyfriend,
who is really a good guy.

326
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:40,200
And now the poor thing
is crying his heart out.

327
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:42,100
Where do I come in?

328
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:45,600
You have so much
influence on her, Father.

329
00:27:45,700 --> 00:27:48,900
Convince her to make up with him.

330
00:27:49,100 --> 00:27:52,600
I'll try. But I can't convince her
of anything she doesn't want.

331
00:27:52,900 --> 00:27:55,200
Go on, it won't hurt you to help her.

332
00:27:55,300 --> 00:27:56,700
Make her happy.

333
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:00,600
Okay.

334
00:28:01,700 --> 00:28:05,100
You're going to get better, okay?
First things first.

335
00:28:08,700 --> 00:28:12,000
The body of Christ. Amen.

336
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:25,900
- You old bitch!
- No, no, Martin!

337
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,600
No, Martin, no!

338
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:15,400
I'm here for Father Benito.

339
00:29:18,500 --> 00:29:20,400
Just a second.

340
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,700
- Father.
- Yes?

341
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:30,300
Someone to see you.
He looks like a hit man.

342
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:31,900
Yes, I'm all ready.

343
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:34,300
- Where are you going?
- To a baptism.

344
00:29:35,100 --> 00:29:37,100
- Where?
- At the <i>hacienda.</i>

345
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,100
What <i>hacienda?</i>

346
00:29:38,300 --> 00:29:42,400
Son, you ask more questions
than the bishop. The <i>hacienda.</i>

347
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,700
Tiburón.

348
00:31:02,900 --> 00:31:04,800
Welcome, Father Benito.

349
00:31:05,100 --> 00:31:07,600
Here I am, Don Chato.
Here I am.

350
00:31:07,700 --> 00:31:09,500
- You look well.
- Yes.

351
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:11,700
- Everything in order?
- Everything.

352
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:16,500
- And this mess with the dollars?
- I exchanged them at a very good price.

353
00:31:16,700 --> 00:31:19,100
- Where is the little one?
- Over there.

354
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:22,400
You're going to get stuffed
with succulent barbecue.

355
00:31:22,500 --> 00:31:26,200
I can't eat too much or I won't fit
into my vestments.

356
00:31:26,300 --> 00:31:30,200
Tell me, when are you going
to visit the clinic?

357
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:39,400
I baptize you with the name
of Maria Elena...

358
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:44,800
...in the name of the Father and
the Son and the Holy Spirit...

359
00:31:44,800 --> 00:31:46,100
...Amen.

360
00:32:09,700 --> 00:32:11,700
Nice pictures?

361
00:32:13,700 --> 00:32:15,900
I'd like to buy some from you.

362
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:18,900
I'd pay you well.

363
00:32:22,300 --> 00:32:24,100
I'm in a lot of them.

364
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:29,200
I work for Mr. Aguilar.

365
00:32:29,300 --> 00:32:33,200
I don't even develop them.
I give him the film and that's it.

366
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:34,400
That's too bad.

367
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:58,500
Galarza wants to see you.

368
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,400
Thanks.

369
00:33:05,700 --> 00:33:07,100
What's up?

370
00:33:07,500 --> 00:33:09,100
Look at this, Ruben.

371
00:33:11,100 --> 00:33:12,800
Chato Aguilar.

372
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:15,100
And Father Benito.

373
00:33:16,100 --> 00:33:18,500
The priest is from your hometown,
right?

374
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:22,900
How did you get these?

375
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:24,800
A present someone brought me.

376
00:33:25,300 --> 00:33:28,000
Someone who wants to fuck over
Chato Aguilar.

377
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:30,200
Chato Aguilar or Father Benito?

378
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:34,200
I could just publish them
and be done with it...

379
00:33:34,300 --> 00:33:36,900
...but it's worth investigating.
It's a big story.

380
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:38,500
Interested?

381
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:44,400
It's my town, everyone knows me there.

382
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:48,700
If you don't want to do it,
I'll give it to Ramiro.

383
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,500
It's up to you.

384
00:33:50,900 --> 00:33:53,600
Fuck it. I'll do it.

385
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:59,400
And not just the hospital center,
there's more.

386
00:33:59,500 --> 00:34:03,400
Then the whole construction
is with Chato Aguilar's money.

387
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:06,800
That's right.
Here are the contracts, costs...

388
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:09,000
Goddamn, this is a lot.

389
00:34:09,100 --> 00:34:10,600
And there's still more.

390
00:34:10,700 --> 00:34:14,300
Here are testimonials
from people in the mountains.

391
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:16,100
What's that about?

392
00:34:16,300 --> 00:34:18,600
About Father Natalio.

393
00:34:19,200 --> 00:34:23,900
A guy named Natalio Perez who
lives in the hills and joined the guerrilla.

394
00:34:24,300 --> 00:34:25,700
Didn't you know?

395
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:29,600
No. Hey, but where did you get
all these facts?

396
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:33,500
Son, a lot of investigating...

397
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:35,100
...and some help.

398
00:34:35,700 --> 00:34:38,600
You know, I should have been
a reporter.

399
00:34:46,200 --> 00:34:49,200
- Thank you. Could I have more lime?
- Oops. Sorry.

400
00:34:50,100 --> 00:34:51,500
Forgive me.

401
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:16,600
<i>Great! This will boost circulation</i>
<i>in a hurry. Damn!</i>

402
00:35:18,600 --> 00:35:20,600
You almost didn't make it, man.

403
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:23,000
See you around.

404
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:26,800
Hello.

405
00:35:36,700 --> 00:35:38,000
Here you are, Don Matias.

406
00:35:38,100 --> 00:35:39,800
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

407
00:35:40,100 --> 00:35:42,100
Have you seen this, Sanjuanera?

408
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:43,700
CHURCH LINKED TO
DRUGS AND GUERRILLA

409
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:45,900
Holy Mother of God!

410
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:52,100
And I thought you were the one
paying for the hospital center.

411
00:35:52,100 --> 00:35:55,100
What we gave would only
have been enough for a clinic.

412
00:35:55,200 --> 00:35:57,400
But damn Father Benito wanted more.

413
00:35:57,500 --> 00:35:59,800
Did you see who signed the article?

414
00:35:59,900 --> 00:36:02,100
- Ruben.
- What Ruben?

415
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:05,600
Ruben de la Rosa.
The son of Don Paco, the heretic.

416
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:07,600
Damn Father Benito, son of a...

417
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:12,600
You have to do something, Gordo.
You're the mayor.

418
00:36:12,700 --> 00:36:14,000
No way!

419
00:36:14,100 --> 00:36:18,400
You have to keep your distance
from priests, like Benito Juarez said.

420
00:36:24,100 --> 00:36:26,600
Father Natalio is late.

421
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:28,700
You can bet he isn't coming.

422
00:36:30,100 --> 00:36:35,800
I told him not to mess with the rebels.
But he was pig-headed!

423
00:36:35,700 --> 00:36:39,100
The accusations against him
aren't clear and refutable.

424
00:36:39,100 --> 00:36:42,000
The journalist states opinion, not facts.

425
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:45,100
He says his people have nothing
to do with guerrillas.

426
00:36:45,300 --> 00:36:46,500
I believe him.

427
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:56,000
And what about Chato Aguilar, Father?

428
00:36:57,800 --> 00:37:01,600
That's an entirely different thing.

429
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:04,600
I always thought... have thought...

430
00:37:04,700 --> 00:37:08,500
...that we shouldn't be too picky
about money for good works.

431
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:12,900
- Even if it comes from Chato Aguilar?
- It's laundering drug money.

432
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:17,800
The true cleansing
is in the eyes of God.

433
00:37:17,900 --> 00:37:21,500
It is bad money that turns good.

434
00:37:36,500 --> 00:37:38,300
Yes, hello?

435
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:40,600
Yes, speaking, Bishop.

436
00:37:40,700 --> 00:37:42,000
I want to tell you...

437
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:44,000
Yes, yes, but...

438
00:37:45,100 --> 00:37:47,500
I understand, Bishop.

439
00:37:47,700 --> 00:37:49,400
Yes, yes.

440
00:37:50,300 --> 00:37:53,700
As you wish. If you'd like,
I can go tomorrow.

441
00:37:55,900 --> 00:37:59,700
Oh. I'll tell him right away.

442
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:02,500
Yes.

443
00:38:03,100 --> 00:38:04,900
Conceived without sin.

444
00:38:10,200 --> 00:38:11,600
Do you want me to go with you?

445
00:38:12,100 --> 00:38:15,200
No, not me.
He doesn't want to see me.

446
00:38:16,300 --> 00:38:18,200
He just wants you to go.

447
00:38:20,700 --> 00:38:22,800
Extension 15, please.

448
00:38:25,100 --> 00:38:26,900
You are a son of a bitch, Ruben!

449
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:31,700
Idiot, dope, faggot, damned apostate!

450
00:38:31,700 --> 00:38:34,200
Renegade, asshole...

451
00:38:34,300 --> 00:38:35,800
...two-legged insect!

452
00:39:00,900 --> 00:39:03,200
It was all a lie, wasn't it, Father?

453
00:39:03,300 --> 00:39:04,600
What?

454
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:08,400
What the newspapers say about
Father Benito.

455
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:10,300
Pure slander, Martin.

456
00:39:11,900 --> 00:39:16,200
I think the devil came to this town
many years ago, Father.

457
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:18,900
He built his lair here.

458
00:39:51,700 --> 00:39:54,400
The bishop is expecting you, Father.

459
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:57,400
Wait here, Martin.

460
00:40:09,200 --> 00:40:12,900
What a joy to see you, son!
Come in, come in.

461
00:40:13,800 --> 00:40:16,800
Put me through to the mayor
of Los Reyes, Sister.

462
00:40:16,900 --> 00:40:18,700
- Have a seat.
- Thank you.

463
00:40:19,100 --> 00:40:23,700
We are here to address
heaven's issues on Earth.

464
00:40:23,700 --> 00:40:25,700
See why I sent you to Los Reyes?

465
00:40:25,900 --> 00:40:29,900
That Benito is a calamity.
Look at the scandal he got us into.

466
00:40:29,900 --> 00:40:34,100
All because he is so stubborn
about having a first-world hospital.

467
00:40:34,100 --> 00:40:36,400
Did you know about Chato Aguilar,
Monsignor?

468
00:40:36,500 --> 00:40:40,300
Where sin is plentiful, grace
will be more plentiful, son.

469
00:40:40,300 --> 00:40:44,500
Even saints make mistakes.
The important thing is to recognize them.

470
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:51,100
Don't make a sour face.
For God all things can be remedied.

471
00:40:52,500 --> 00:40:56,000
I already spoke with the director
of that rag.

472
00:40:56,100 --> 00:40:59,000
We're going to publish a rebuttal.

473
00:40:59,500 --> 00:41:01,800
You will write it.

474
00:41:05,300 --> 00:41:06,700
Yes, Sister?

475
00:41:08,100 --> 00:41:09,600
Hello?

476
00:41:15,200 --> 00:41:16,900
Gordo.

477
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:19,300
The bishop is on the phone.

478
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:22,600
Those priests. I'm not going.

479
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:26,200
No, no.

480
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:27,800
At your service, Bishop.

481
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:33,100
No, no. It's just a lot of noise
about nothing.

482
00:41:33,900 --> 00:41:37,900
No, Bishop. Don't say that.
I can't say I gave all that money.

483
00:41:37,900 --> 00:41:40,400
It's in the millions. They'll lynch me.

484
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,900
Oh, that's okay.

485
00:41:43,500 --> 00:41:48,000
If you take responsibility for half,
I'll vouch for the other half.

486
00:41:48,800 --> 00:41:52,500
Fine. Perfect. I'll send the fax
to the newspaper tomorrow.

487
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,000
Yes, Bishop.

488
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:56,900
See you later.

489
00:41:59,200 --> 00:42:02,800
- Will everything be all right now?
- Yes, yes, yes.

490
00:42:04,400 --> 00:42:07,400
There's no worse politics
than black politics.

491
00:42:07,900 --> 00:42:09,200
Fucking priests.

492
00:42:09,500 --> 00:42:13,700
Don't let your party hear you,
they'll burn you alive.

493
00:42:13,800 --> 00:42:17,500
I govern for the people,
not the party.

494
00:42:18,300 --> 00:42:19,600
No shit?

495
00:42:25,100 --> 00:42:28,700
For his activities, I'll take Father
Natalio out of his community.

496
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:31,400
He swears there are no guerrillas
in his area.

497
00:42:31,900 --> 00:42:36,000
I'll lock him up with the nuns.
Let him take care of them.

498
00:42:36,700 --> 00:42:40,200
- Bishop, if you will allow me an opinion...
- Relax, son.

499
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:43,800
I know how tiresome all this is for you.

500
00:42:44,100 --> 00:42:48,900
But first we have to get the work done.
Then you will come to my side...

501
00:42:48,900 --> 00:42:51,000
...and learn to run the diocese.

502
00:42:52,600 --> 00:42:55,200
- Thank you.
- Goodbye, son.

503
